==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*wirāz'', from Indo-European ''*wīrō-''.  Germanic cognates include Old Frisian ''wer'', Old Saxon ''wer'', Old High German ''wer'', Old Norse [[verr]], Gothic [[𐍅𐌴𐍂]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[vir]], Old Irish [[fer]] (Welsh [[gwr]]), Baltic ''*wira-'' (Lithuanian [[viras|vīras]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /weɹ/

===Noun===
'''wer''' ''m''
# a [[man]], a [[husband]]

